<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>{{.Title}}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Material+Symbols+Outlined:opsz,wght,FILL,GRAD@24,400,0,0&icon_names=potted_plant" />
</head>
<body>
    <main>
        <article>
            <h1 class="index-title"><span class="material-symbols-outlined">potted_plant</span>Note Garden</h1>
            <p>Hi, I'm Andres, a software engineer. You can find more about me on <a href="https://andresfelipemendez.com">my website</a>.</p>
            <p>This is my digital garden. It's a collection of notes, ideas, and thoughts that grow and evolve over time. Unlike a blog, these aren't polished articles, just working notes for myself. They're interconnected, often incomplete, and always changing.</p>
            <p>Since I started using AI to code, I've felt more anxious about my own understanding. So I decided to take note-taking seriously. Writing is the work. Gaining knowledge matters more than ever, and these notes are how I make sure the learning stays with me.</p>
            <p>This site is open source. The static site generator is written in Go with automated deployments via GitHub Actions and <a href="https://github.com/andresfelipemendez/cluster-config">ArgoCD</a>. Check out the <a href="https://github.com/andresfelipemendez/garden">source code on GitHub</a>.</p>
            <section class="notes-section">
                <h2>Notes</h2>
                <ul class="note-list">
                {{range .Notes}}
                    <li><span class="note-date">{{.Updated}}</span> <a href="{{.Href}}">{{.Title}}</a></li>
                {{end}}
                </ul>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
